The police in Modjadjiskloof outside Tzaneen have launched a manhunt for a woman who allegedly abducted a child in a suburb outside Modjadjiskloof on Wednesday morning. It’s understood the woman requested accommodation at the child’s parents’ home. Colonel Cecil Machimana said: “On Wednesday morning, the child’s mother went to the local supermarket and when she came back, she found that the suspect had disappeared with the five-month-old baby girl.” Machimana said, from preliminary police investigations, it was revealed that the suspect boarded a taxi from Modjadjiskloof to Makhado and later went to a hiding spot. The suspect was last seen wearing a purple towel and pink short-sleeved T-shirt. She has short hair and is average height. -TNA Reporter